00:01:14.940 --> 00:01:17.910 align:middle line:10%
We're all in the field,
and our subatomic particles

00:01:17.910 --> 00:01:20.290 align:middle line:10%
make up the field.

00:01:20.290 --> 00:01:24.450 align:middle line:84%
So, because we
are energy, energy

00:01:24.450 --> 00:01:29.040 align:middle line:84%
is changing at every moment
at the subatomic level.

00:01:29.040 --> 00:01:32.050 align:middle line:84%
Nothing is an
actual anything yet.

00:01:32.050 --> 00:01:35.070 align:middle line:84%
It's every possible
state all at once.

00:01:35.070 --> 00:01:38.250 align:middle line:84%
And what they've
found is what turns

00:01:38.250 --> 00:01:44.370 align:middle line:84%
that potential of something into
something real is an observer.

00:01:44.370 --> 00:01:48.450 align:middle line:84%
So our consciousness,
our ability to observe,

00:01:48.450 --> 00:01:54.000 align:middle line:84%
our ability to intend,
also makes us a creator.

00:01:54.000 --> 00:01:55.800 align:middle line:84%
>> Lynne's intention
experiments,

00:01:55.800 --> 00:01:59.400 align:middle line:84%
running since 2007, are
some of the first controlled

00:01:59.400 --> 00:02:03.120 align:middle line:84%
explorations of the
power of mass intention.

00:02:03.120 --> 00:02:05.760 align:middle line:84%
In these experiments,
she invites an audience

00:02:05.760 --> 00:02:07.860 align:middle line:84%
to send a specific
thought to affect

00:02:07.860 --> 00:02:10.770 align:middle line:84%
a target, after which
a team of scientists

00:02:10.770 --> 00:02:14.550 align:middle line:84%
calculate the results to
measure possible change.

00:02:14.550 --> 00:02:17.880 align:middle line:84%
>> I've run 40
intention experiments,

00:02:17.880 --> 00:02:22.920 align:middle line:84%
everything from trying to make
plants grow faster and seeds

00:02:22.920 --> 00:02:27.030 align:middle line:84%
grow faster, to purifying
water, to lowering violence

00:02:27.030 --> 00:02:30.090 align:middle line:84%
in war-torn areas
or violent areas,

00:02:30.090 --> 00:02:33.330 align:middle line:90%
to even healing someone of PTSD.

00:02:33.330 --> 00:02:37.590 align:middle line:84%
And of those 40, 35 have shown
measurable, positive, mostly

00:02:37.590 --> 00:02:40.470 align:middle line:84%
significant effects
as measured by teams

00:02:40.470 --> 00:02:44.130 align:middle line:84%
of scientists in different
prestigious universities.

00:02:44.130 --> 00:02:48.270 align:middle line:10%
So we've got lots of evidence
that thoughts are things

00:02:48.270 --> 00:02:50.550 align:middle line:10%
that affect other things.

00:02:50.550 --> 00:02:54.210 align:middle line:10%
>> Of particular significance to
Lynne is her peace experiments,

00:02:54.210 --> 00:02:58.020 align:middle line:10%
which include the two she has
now done on the 10th and 20th

00:02:58.020 --> 00:03:01.260 align:middle line:10%
